    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PACA35AE2C051E365"
      },
      "description": "### Should be 1 for proper functioning\n\nThe active controller count metric indicates whether the broker is currently the controller for the cluster.\n\nThe metric will either be 0 or 1, with 1 showing that the broker is currently the controller (Since we have a single broker setup, this should always be 1).\n\n#### Possible reasons\n* At all times, only one broker should be the controller, and one broker must always be the controller in the cluster.<br><br>\n* If two brokers say that they are currently the controller, this means that you have a problem where a controller thread that should have exited has become stuck\n\n*Kafka the Definitive Guide*, Narkhede N., Shapira G., Palino T.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "max": 2,
          "min": 0,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 19,
      "options": {
        "minVizHeight": 75,
        "minVizWidth": 75,
        "orientation": "auto",
        "reduceOptions": {
