    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PACA35AE2C051E365"
      },
      "description": "### Should be 0 for proper functioning\n\nProvided on each broker in a cluster, gives a count of the number of partitions for which the broker is the leader replica, where the follower replicas are not caught up.\n\n#### Possible reasons\n* Steady (unchanging) value reported by many of the brokers in a cluster normally indicates that one of the brokers in the cluster is off‚Äêline.<br><br>\n\n* If value is fluctuating, or if the number is steady but there are no brokers offline, this typically indicates a performance issue in the cluster.\n\n*Kafka the Definitive Guide*, Narkhede N., Shapira G., Palino T.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "max": 1,
          "min": -1,
          "thresholds": {
